RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 32000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEKILA showed the way in hand just off the inside coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun three wide for home, edged away under a drive holding well to the finish kept to task. TONIGHT WE LOVE coaxed from the gate, chased two then three wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled five wide into upper stretch and ran on to secure the place honors. ALWAJD chased six to seven paths off the inside down the backstretch and through the turn, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, went eight wide into upper stretch and offered up a mild kick to secure the show honors. CANDLESTICK MAKER chased four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled six wide into upper stretch, weakened. FROSTY INVASION chased three wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, tipped three to four wide into upper stretch, weakened in the drive. LORDHEARMYPRAYER coaxed from the start, chased five wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled six wide at the head of the stretch and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 36000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Wi ll Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DANCING SOPHIA moved off the rail early then settled off the pace, pursued the leader in the two path for most of the turn, shifted four wide inside the five-sixteenths, gained to make a bid coming to the quarter-pole, jostled with BRISKY FROLIC while carried six wide into upper stretch, gained the lead before the three-sixteenths, responded well into the final furlong, drifted out late and held under strong urging. RUN DEVIL was hustled from the start, tracked the pace on the outside, came under urging outside the half-mile pole, went three then four wide early on the turn, moved to the five path late on that bend, came seven wide into the stretch, chased outside into the final furlong, made a bid in the middle of the track at the sixteenth-pole but was turned away and settled for the place. APRIL ANTICS bobbled outward at the start, settled off the pace, was urged along passing the five-eighths then dropped back, went five then six wide around the turn, came eight wide into the stretch and lacked the needed response while clear for the show. BRISKY FROLIC went to the front then moved clear, extended the advantage near the nine-sixteenths, went two then three wide around the turn, was challenged by the winner outside the quarter-pole, jostled with that foe while floating five wide into upper stretch then lost the advantage, dropped back into the final furlong and weakened. SYNONYMOUS was last into stride, moved up under urging on the outside, went four then five wide around the turn, dropped to the three path coming to the quarter-pole and came up empty. IN TRAFFIC settled off the pace, dropped back while saving ground around the turn, turned into the stretch in the two path and had nothing left.

ENTRY.NAME: In Traffic
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, saved ground, came up empty

ENTRY.NAME: Synonymous
ENTRY.COMMENT: last into stride,mvd up outside,4-5wide turn,3w1/4,empty

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 32000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SCOOTSCOOT broke out at the start bumping WARRIOR RICHARD into STEADY PROGRESS, showed the way in hand just off the inside coming under coaxing near the five-sixteenths, angled four wide into upper stretch, edged clear under a drive to prevail. WARRIOR RICHARD broke in at the start and was bumped by SCOOTSCOOT and in turn bumped STEADY PROGRESS, chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the turn, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, angled five wide into upper stretch and ran on to secure the place honors. STORMANDY chased three wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled out seven wide into upper stretch and kept on to secure the show honors. STEADY PROGRESS got bumped at the start by WARRIOR RICHARD due to pressure from SCOOTSCOOT, chased three wide under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, tipped four wide at the top of the stretch and improved position. SCREEN DOOR hustled from the gate, chased five then four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled six wide into upper stretch and weakened. EL GRAN CUYAYA chased three then two wide under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and tired. FROSTY HOLIDAY hesitated at the start breaking last and conceding five to six lengths to the front before settling into stride seven paths off the inside down the backstretch, tucked five wide through the turn and went six to seven wide into upper stretch, then trailed throughout when eased home to the finish well behind the rest.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY FIRST LOVE stumbled at the start but broke with the field, stalked the pace down the backstretch, issued a challenge in the four path around the turn, took the lead coming to the quarter-pole, shook clear under a right-handed crop inside the furlong marker, switched to a left-handed crop at the sixteenth-pole and proved much the best under strong urging. SA FORADADA was hustled from the gate, moved out then was urged along off the pace, went three wide early on the turn then shifted five wide in pursuit of the leader, gained to make an outside bid in upper stretch, fought outside of the runner-up into the final furlong and proved no match while clear for the place. DIAMOND COLLECTOR disputed the pace on the outside then in the three path around the turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive into the final furlong and weakened while clear for the show. GAGLIANO was urged along on the outside, dropped from the four path to the two path around the turn and was no factor. ALPINE QUEEN was hustled from the start, contested the pace on the inside of a foe, vied in the two path while inside rivals around the turn and faded. RAFFINITY drifted out at the start, tracked the pace on the outside, dropped back under urging late on the backstretch, went five to six wide around the turn and retreated.

ENTRY.NAME: Raffinity
ENTRY.OWNER: Imperio Michael Rodriguez Rudy R and Gurdon Andrew

CALY BALI broke in at the start bumping MAJOR HOULIHAN into WOKE UP A DIVA, pressed the pace three wide between foes under coaxing from three furlongs out, swung four wide into upper stretch and weakened. WOKE UP A DIVA bumped at the start by MAJOR HOULIHAN due to pressure from CALY BALI, chased three wide growing detached at the tail of the field, angled five wide at the top of the stretch and trailed when eased home to the finish.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHINFULL showed speed on the outside then chased the pace, went five then four wide around the turn, gained at the five-sixteenths then made a bid, took a short lead in upper stretch, battled outside of the runner-up in the final furlong and narrowly prevailed under strong urging. BACKED BY GOLD brushed with a foe early, disputed the pace on the inside of a rival, shook off that foe in the two path midway through the turn, spun three wide into the stretch under pressure then lost the advantage to the winner around the three-sixteenths, fought on while dueling with that foe, drifted out some near the sixteenth-pole and just missed while able to get the place. PREPOSTEROUS brushed with a rival at the start, settled on the outside, was roused six then five wide around the turn, chased outside in the stretch and finished willingly to just get the show. SHADOLAMO broke out and brushed with a foe, was urged along off the pace, moved from three to five wide around the turn, came six wide into the stretch and improved to just miss the show. BERN ROSEY BERN showed speed between rivals then chased the pace, dropped back while moving from the four path to the two path around the turn and tired. HOLIDAY JAZZ brushed with an opponent early, showed speed between horses then contested the pace on the outside, vied in the three path around the turn, spun four wide into the stretch and faded. STARTED WITH STARS was urged along near the back, moved from the rail to the three path while dropping back on the turn and faltered.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT WORKER dueled from the two path with PERSISTENT DANGER early on before vying inside a pair through the turn as BRACIOLE joined them stacked in the five path, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths and went four wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive and edged away gamely inside the final sixteenth to prevail safe on the wire. BRACIOLE five paths off the inside down the backstretch, advanced half a mile from home to vied outside a pair through the turn coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung six wide into upper stretch and fought on to the finish but was ultimately repelled at the end. PERSISTENT DANGER led early on before being engaged in a duel from the four path with MIDNIGHT WORKER to the inside, got joined half a mile from home outside and vied from the four path between foes through the turn under coaxing with five-sixteenths to go, swung five wide into upper stretch, got shaken off near the eighth pole and weakened in the late stages. STORIED FELLA brushed at the start by GOT THE GOLD, who broke outwards, chased three then two wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, swung four wide into upper stretch and weakened. GOT THE GOLD broke out at the start brushing the aforementioned foe, chased six to seven paths off the inside down the backstretch and then three wide through the turn, went seven to eight wide into upper stretch and weakened. TWO DOWN hustled from the gate, chased three then two wide under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, angled five to six wide into upper stretch and made no impact. AVA K'S BOY chased just off the inside until tucked inside half a mile from home put to coaxing, angled four to five wide into upper stretch and faltered. ABUNDANT HONOR chased six then five wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled six to seven wide into upper stretch and folded.
